title: Liberal Party Officially Ditches Net Zero By 2050 Policy | 10 News+
description: The Liberal Party has formally announced it will ditch its net zero by 2050 target, following in the footsteps of their Nationals colleagues. Liberal leader Sussan Ley says their priority is on reducing energy prices for Australians, and Nationals leader David Littleproud insists his party believes in the science of climate change. Meanwhile, Prime Minister Albanese called the Coalition a “clown show” that is internally divided. title: Widow’s Wish To Be Buried Next To Husband Crushed Due To Rezoning | 10 News+
description: A 76-year-old woman who’s been working on her farm her whole life has found herself unable to be buried next to her husband, because the land has been rezoned by the government. Gaye Wheatley, and dozens of farmers in central New South Wales, have been threatened with fines if they touch the soil or the trees on the land they have toiled on for generations. title: Cynthia Erivo Protects Ariana Grande As Fan Rushes Star | 10 News
description: Cynthia Erivo jumped between Ariana Grande and a man who broke through barricades and grabbed the singer on the yellow carpet at the ‘Wicked: For Good’ Singapore premiere, with footage showing Grande visibly shaken as security rushed in.  The man was quickly restrained and later identified by fans as Johnson Wen, the self-styled 'Pyjama Man' known for storming stages and confronting celebrities.  Wen posted his own video after the incident, sparking fierce backlash from fans who accused him of assault and disrespecting Grande’s safety.  Erivo and co-star Michelle Yeoh comforted Grande following the scare, as the cast continued their whirlwind global tour for the ‘Wicked’ sequel  Join the conversation and follow us on: TikTok: http://www.tiktok.com/@10NewsAU/ Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/10NewsAU/ Twitter: http://twitter.com/10NewsAU Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/10NewsAU/  10 News airs at 5pm, seven nights a week in your local market on Network 10. title: Two Dead, 18 Injured After Truck Crashes Into South Korean Market | 10 News
description: Two people have been killed and 18 others injured after a light truck crashed into a market in South Korea on Thursday.  CCTV shows the vehicle speeding through a passageway lined with stalls before ploughing into a store at an outdoor market in Bucheon.  Authorities say the driver, a man in his 60s who was not intoxicated, has been arrested, with sudden unintended acceleration believed to be the cause.  Local media report two people went into cardiac arrest at the scene and were later confirmed dead. title: Settlers Torch West Bank Mosque As Violence Surges And Condemnations Grow | 10 News
description: Israeli settlers have torched and vandalised a mosque in the West Bank town of Deir Istiya, burning copies of the Quran and spray-painting threatening messages in an escalation of attacks on Palestinian communities.  The assault comes just days after Israeli leaders, including the president and military chiefs, issued rare condemnations of settler violence following a separate rampage that saw cars, property and even soldiers targeted.  Troops were sent to investigate Thursday’s arson, but no suspects have been identified, fuelling long-standing claims that settlers operate with near-total impunity under Benjamin Netanyahu’s right-wing government.  UN monitors say settler attacks have reached record levels, displacing thousands of Palestinians as new outposts sprawl further across occupied land. title: Blue Origin Launches Satellites To Mars In NASA Mission | 10 News
description: The Blue Origin space venture of billionaire Jeff Bezos has successfully launched its towering rocket from Florida.  New Glenn took flight from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station on Thursday, carrying two satellites on their way to Mars in the company's first NASA-scale science mission.  A live webcast shows the rocket’s reusable first-stage booster separating from the upper stage a few minutes after launch before it flew back to Earth.  The launch followed several days of delays due to cloudy skies and a geomagnetic storm and marks the first mission flown by the company since New Glenn's inaugural test launch on January 16.
